@startuml How It Works - Canonical Sequence

title IntegrateWise OS: Slack Message → Notion Write Flow

actor User
participant Slack
participant Hub as "Hub\n(Auth/Policy/Router)"
participant Loader as "AI Loader\n(Transform)"
participant Spine as "Spine\n(Canonical Store)"
participant Brain as "Brain\n(Memory)"
participant Agents as "Agents\n(Workflow)"
participant Approval as "Approval\n(Workflow)"
participant Notion as "Notion API"
participant Render as "Render\n(Output)"
participant Audit as "Audit Log"

User -> Slack: Send message
Slack -> Hub: 1. Webhook (message.created)\nHeaders: X-IW-Signature, X-IW-Timestamp, X-IW-Idempotency-Key

Hub -> Hub: 2. Authenticate (HMAC-SHA256)
Hub -> Hub: 3. Evaluate policy (RBAC/ABAC)
Hub -> Hub: 4. Route to Slack connector

Hub -> Loader: 5. Authenticated request

Loader -> Loader: 6. Parse Slack payload
Loader -> Loader: 7. Map to Conversation entity
Loader -> Loader: 8. Validate Spine constraints

Loader -> Spine: 9. Create Conversation entity

Spine -> Spine: 10. Create entity (UUID v4)
Spine -> Spine: 11. Link to related entities

Spine -> Brain: 12. Entity created event

Brain -> Brain: 13. Index Conversation
Brain -> Brain: 14. Compute linkage scores
Brain -> Brain: 15. Check for duplicates

Brain -> Agents: 16. Memory updated

Agents -> Agents: 17. Evaluate triggers (Brain Agent)
Agents -> Brain: 18. Retrieve relevant context
Agents -> Agents: 19. Generate action plan\nAction: Create Notion page

Agents -> Approval: 20. Request approval

Approval -> Approval: 21. Check approval rules
Approval -> Agents: 22. Approval granted

Agents -> Hub: 23. Approved action

Hub -> Hub: 24. Route to Notion connector (write)
Hub -> Hub: 25. Check write permissions

Hub -> Notion: 26. Create Notion page\n(Write API call)

Notion -> Hub: 27. Success response

Hub -> Render: 28. Render dashboard update (optional)

Render -> Render: 29. Apply template
Render -> Render: 30. Export to target

Render -> Audit: 31. Render complete

Hub -> Audit: 32. Log audit event\n{workspace_id, actor_id, action_type, resource_type, resource_id, timestamp, request_id, policy_id, outcome}
Hub -> Hub: 33. Record usage metrics

@enduml
